{"questionId":"9076791","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The attenuation values for fat and muscle at different X-ray energies are shown.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4863/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-14_om_09.40.21.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/HP3/ENG/TZ2/15.b\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State what is meant by half-value thickness in X-ray imaging.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>the thickness of tissue that reduces the intensity <strong>«</strong>of the X-rays<strong>» </strong>by a half</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x_{\\frac{1}{2}}} = \\frac{{\\ln 2}}{\\mu }\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>ln</mi>\n      <mo>⁡</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>μ</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x_{\\frac{1}{2}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is the half value thickness and <em>μ</em> is attenuation coefficient</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Symbols must be defined for mark to be&nbsp;</em><em>awarded</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076791","referenceCode":"18M.3.HL.TZ2.15b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"State what is meant by half-value thickness in X-ray imaging.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (A